Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lincolnshire): habitational name from a place in Norfolk, so named from Old English <i>græs</i>, <i>gærs</i> ‘grass(land), pasturage’ + <i>hām</i> ‘homestead’ or <i>hamm</i> ‘enclosure hemmed in by water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Grisham","meanings":["English: variant of   Gresham  . This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Branche","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a nickname for a blonde, from <i>blanche</i>, feminine of Old French <i>blanc</i> ‘white’ (of Germanic origin). It came to be associated with the notion of whiteness as indicating purity, and was introduced into England as a given name by the Normans. A pale complexion combined with light hair was long an ideal of beauty in Europe (compare Modern English <i>fair</i>, which at first meant ‘beautiful’ and then, from the 16th century, ‘light in colouring’)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Peter De Branche De Gresham was born in 1235, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Peter de Braunche, was 34 and his mother, Joan, was 29. He had at least 1 son with Joan De Branche De Gresham. He died in Gresham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1235–":"1235–Surnud","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1239–Female":"1239–Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1206–Female":"1206–Surnud","about 1260":"umbes 1260","1206":"1206","1239":"1239","1235":"1235","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","1260":"1260","1229":"1229","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gresham, Norfolk, England":"Gresham, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1235–":"1235–Kuollut","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1235–Male":"1235–Kuollut","1239–Female":"1239–Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1206–Female":"1206–Kuollut","about 1260":"noin 1260","1206":"1206","1239":"1239","1235":"1235","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","1260":"1260","1229":"1229","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gresham, Norfolk, England":"Gresham, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1235–":"1235–Décédé","1230–Male":"1230–Décédé","1235–Male":"1235–Décédé","1239–Female":"1239–Décédée","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1206–Female":"1206–Décédée","about 1260":"environ 1260","1206":"1206","1239":"1239","1235":"1235","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","1260":"1260","1229":"1229","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Gresham, Norfolk, England":"Gresham, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Peter De Branche De Gresham est né en 1235, à Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Sir Peter de Braunche, avait 34 ans et sa mère, Joan, avait 29 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joan De B